        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "are all at most 25/13. This can be checked by a long numerical calculation, which we omit in favor of some shortcuts: note that ADFH and BEJ are contained in circular sectors centered at A and B, respectively, of radius 25/13 and angle less than 1/3, while CGF H is a rectangle with diameter CF < 25/13.",
        "bbox": [
          0.556390978273191,
          0.3052325583505595,
          0.9191729396638392,
          0.39098837211885956
        ],
        "order": 9
